quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,49,"And of everything We have created pairs, that you may remember (the Grace of Allâh)."
  51,50,"So flee to Allâh (from His Torment to His Mercy - Islâmic Monotheism). Verily, I (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) am a plain warner to you from Him.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.50) See the footnote of (Verse 3:85).
  51,51,"And set not up (or worship not) any other ilâh (god) along with Allâh [Glorified be He (Alone), Exalted above all that they associate as partners with Him]. Verily, I (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) am a plain warner to you from Him."
  52,40,"Or is it that you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) ask a wage from them (for your preaching of Islâmic Monotheism) so that they are burdened with a load of debt?"
  52,41,"Or that the Ghaib (Unseen) is with them, and they write it down?"
  52,42,"Or do they intend a plot (against you O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم)? But those who disbelieve (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) are themselves plotted against!"
  53,34,"And gave a little, then stopped (giving)?"
  53,35,"Is with him the knowledge of the Unseen so that he sees?"
  53,36,"Or is he not informed with what is in the Pages (Scripture) of Mûsâ (Moses),"
  54,25,""
  54,26,"Tomorrow they will come to know who is the liar, the insolent one!"
  54,27,"Verily, We are sending the she-camel as a test for them. So watch them [O Sâlih عليه السلام], and be patient!"
  55,19,"He has let loose the two seas (the salt and fresh water) meeting together."
  55,20,"Between them is a barrier which none of them can transgress."
  55,21,"Then which of the Blessings of your Lord will you both (jinn and men) deny?"
  56,10,"And those foremost [(in Islâmic Faith of Monotheism and in performing righteous deeds) in the life of this world on the very first call for to embrace Islâm] will be foremost (in Paradise)."
  56,11,"These will be the nearest (to Allâh)."
  56,12,"In the Gardens of Delight (Paradise)."
  57,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth glorifies Allâh - and He is the All-Mighty, All-Wise."
  57,2,"His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. It is He Who gives life and causes death: and He is Able to do all things."
  57,3,"He is the First (nothing is before Him) and the Last (nothing is after Him), the Most High (nothing is above Him) and the Most Near (nothing is nearer than Him). And He is the All-Knower of every thing."